title: Print, "Female Egyptian Head, Year 1937 Collar", 1937
description: This head-and-neck left profile view features a close-fitting headdress with an ear flap; and a collar, perhaps fabricated of metal, displaying the numerals 1, 9, 3, and 7, separated by vertical lines in groups of three. Three narrow, triangular shapes comprise a drop earring, extending downward from behind the flap.
